Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n| nationality        = [[India]]n\n| occupation         = Film and television actor\n| yearsactive        = 1984 \u2013 present<ref name=\"Bhabhi Ji Ghar Par Hain\u2019s Aasif Sheikh aka Vibhuti Narayan on rewind\">{{cite news | url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/bhabhi-ji-ghar-par-hains-aasif-sheikh-aka-vibhuti-narayan-on-rewind/ | title=Bhabhi Ji Ghar Par Hain's Aasif Sheikh aka Vibhuti Narayan on rewind | work= Bollywood Life |author=Urmimala Banerjee |date=9 June 2016 |accessdate=28 December 2018}}</ref>\n| known_for          = ''[[Bhabi Ji Ghar Par Hai!]]''<br/>''[[Yes Boss (TV series)|Yes Boss]]''<br>''[[Karan Arjun]]''<br>''[[Yaara Dildara]]''<br>''[[Rama O Rama]]''\n| website            = \n| spouse             =  Zeba Sheikh\n|children= 2\n| home_town          = [[Varanasi]], India\n}}\n\n'''Aasif Sheikh''' is an [[Indian people|Indian]] film, stage and television actor. He played the role of Prince Ajay Singh in India's first TV serial, ''[[Hum Log (TV series)|Hum Log]]''. He has appeared in numerous Bollywood films and TV serials. He acted in the TV series [[Yes Boss (TV series)|Yes Boss]] which ran from 1999 to 2009. Presently running sitcom series ''[[Bhabiji Ghar Par Hain!]]'', has him  playing the role of ''Vibhuti Narayan Mishra''.\n\n==Personal life==\nSheikh spent his childhood in [[Varanasi]], [[Uttar Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web |url =https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/events/lucknow/my-cousins-considered-me-a-dud-actor-aasif-sheikh/articleshow/62085654.cms|title =My cousins considered me a dud actor: Aasif Sheikh|work =[[The Times of India]] |author=Meera Vohra |date=16 December 2016 |accessdate=28 December 2018}}</ref> He is married to Zeba Sheikh, with whom he has two children, daughter Maryam Nastasia and son Alyjah Iman.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u092f\u0947 \u0939\u0948\u0902 '\u092d\u093e\u092c\u0940\u091c\u0940...' \u0915\u0947 \u0935\u093f\u092d\u0942\u0924\u093f \u0928\u093e\u0930\u093e\u092f\u0923 \u0915\u0940 \u092c\u0947\u091f\u0940, \u0926\u0947\u0916\u0947\u0902 Family \u0915\u0940 Unseen Photos |url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/ent-tv-bhabi-ji-ghar-par-hai-actor-aashif-sheikh-unseen-family-photos-news-hindi-5529502-pho.html |accessdate=6 March 2020 |work=Dainik Bhaskar |date=16 February 2017 |language=hi}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=iaasifsheikh |number =695124434751852544 |title=@Neeshasharma7 my son..Alyjah Iman...daughter..Maryam Nastassia...|date=3 February 2016 |accessdate=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Theatre==\n\nHe is associated with Indian People's Theatre Association, Mumbai. He has acted in plays like ''[[Kabuliwala (short story)|Kabuliwala]]'', ''Aakhri Shama'', ''Simla Coffee House'', ''Hum Deewane Hum Parwane'', ''Ek Baar Phir'' and ''Aaall izz Well with Shuturmurgh''. One of his popular plays is ''U-Turn'' co-starring [[Poonam Dhillon]].<ref>{{cite web |title=INDIAN PEOPLE'S THEATRE ASSOCIATION - Plays |url=http://www.iptamumbai.in/Plays |website=IPTAMumbai |accessdate=2 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\nSheikh started his career with ''[[Hum Log (TV series)|Hum Log]]'', India's first daily television show.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://dailypost.in/lifestyle/fashion-and-beauty/49738-a-straightforward-man |title=A Straightforward Man |website=[[Daily Post India]] |author=Daily Life writer |date=21 October 2015 |accessdate=28 December 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222163412/http://dailypost.in/lifestyle/fashion-and-beauty/49738-a-straightforward-man |archivedate=22 December 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Feature films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role\n|-\n| 1988 ||''[[Rama O Rama]]''|| Vickey (Sonu)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1990 ||''[[Qayamat Ki Raat]] ''|| Awinash\n|-\n|''[[Agneekaal]] ''|| Aadesh\n|-\n|''[[Muqaddar Ka Badshaah]]''|| Ashok Singh\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | 1991 ||''Pyar Ka Saudagar''|| Arun Verma\n|-\n|''[[Yaara Dildara]]''|| Rajesh Mehra\n|-\n|''[[Haque (film)|Haque]]''|| Sanjay\n|-\n|''[[Swarg Jaisaa Ghar]]''|| Amar\n|-\n|''Lahu Luhaan''||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 1992 ||''Naya Sawan''||\n|-\n|''Sone Ki Zanjeer''|| Manish\n|-\n|''[[Apradhi (1992 film)|Apradhi]]''|| Chander\n|-\n| 1994 ||''[[Ishq Mein Jeena Ishq Mein Marna]] ''||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 1995 ||''[[Zamaana Deewana]]''|| Bobby\n|-\n|''[[Kartavya (1995 film)|Kartavya]]''||\n|-\n|''[[Karan Arjun]]''|| Suraj Singh\n|-\n|''[[The Don (1995 film)|The Don]]''|| Nagesh\n|-\n|''[[Paandav]]'' ||\n|-\n|''[[Taaqat (1995 film)|Taaqat]]''|| Maniya\n|-\n|''[[Ham Sab Chor Hain (1995 film)|Ham Sab Chor Hain]]''|| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 1996 ||''[[Duniyaa Jhukti Hai]]''||\n|-\n|''[[Agni Prem]] ''||\n|-\n|''[[Army (1996 film)|Army]]''|| Rahul\n|-\n|''Muqadma''||\n|-\n|''[[Apne Dam Par]]''||\n|-\n|''Bal Bramhachari''|| Ranjeet\n|-\n|''[[Chhote Sarkar (1996 film)|Chhote Sarkar]]''|| Lobo\n|- \n| rowspan=\"7\" | 1997 ||''[[Mrityudaata]]''|| Mohanlal's son\n|-\n|''[[Banarasi Babu (1997 film)|Banarasi Babu]]''|| Vikram\n|-\n|''[[Auzaar]]''|| Inspector Bhutey\n|-\n|''[[Kaun Sachcha Kaun Jhootha]]''|| John D'Souza\n|-\n|''[[Daadagiri]]''|| Monty\n|-\n|''[[Aur Pyar Ho Gaya]]''|| Rohit Malhotra\n|-\n|''[[Ek Phool Teen Kante]]''||\n|- \n| rowspan=\"5\" | 1998 ||''[[Miss 420]]''|| Arvind\n|-\n|''[[Pyaar Kiya To Darna Kya (1998 film)|Pyaar Kiya To Darna Kya]]''|| Thakur Vijay Singh's brother\n|-\n|''[[Zulm-O-Sitam]]''|| Guy who teased 'Meena'\n|-\n|''[[Bandhan (1998 film)|Bandhan]]''|| Police Inspector\n|-\n|''[[Pardesi Babu]]''|| Nandu\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 1999 ||''[[Sikandar Sadak Ka]]''|| Bunty Chawla\n|-\n|''[[Haseena Maan Jaayegi]]''|| Pritam Nath\n|-\n|''[[Pyaar Koi Khel Nahin]]''||\n|-\n|''Jaalsaaz''|| Ranjit Rai\n|- \n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2000 ||  ''Daak Bangla''||\n|-\n|''[[Kunwara]]''|| Ajay\n|-\n|''[[Deewane]]''|| Vishal's cousin\n|-\n|''[[Karobaar: The Business of Love]]''|| Ramlal's son\n|-\