{"title_page": "2012\u201313 Northampton Town F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n| season             = 2012\u201313\n| manager            = [[Aidy Boothroyd]]\n| chairman           = [[David Cardoza]]\n| stadium            = [[Sixfields Stadium]]\n| league             = [[2012\u201313 Football League Two|League Two]]\n| league result      = 6th - Play-off Finalists\n| cup1               = [[2012\u201313 FA Cup|FA Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = [[2012\u201313 FA Cup#First round|First round]]\n| cup2               = [[2012\u201313 Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n| cup2 result        = [[2012\u201313 Football League Cup#Second round|Second round]]\n| cup3               = [[2012\u201313 Football League Trophy|League Trophy]]\n| cup3 result        = [[2012\u201313 Football League Trophy#Area Quarter Finals|Q/F Final (South)]]\n| league topscorer   = [[Adebayo Akinfenwa|Bayo Akinfenwa]] (16)\n| season topscorer   = [[Adebayo Akinfenwa|Bayo Akinfenwa]] (17)\n| highest attendance = 7,471 vs [[Barnet F.C.|Barnet]]\n| lowest attendance  = 1,561 vs [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]\n| average attendance = 4,785\n| prevseason         = [[2011\u201312 Northampton Town F.C. season|2011\u201312]]\n| nextseason         = [[2013\u201314 Northampton Town F.C. season|2013\u201314]]\n}}\nThe '''2012\u201313 season''' was [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]'s 116th season of existence and their fourth competitive season in [[Football League Two|League Two]]. Along with competing in League Two, the club also participated in the [[2012\u201313 FA Cup|FA Cup]], [[2012\u201313 Football League Cup|League Cup]] and [[2012\u201313 Football League Trophy|Football League Trophy]].\n\nThe season covers the period from 1 July 2012 to 30 June 2013.\n\n==Competitions==\n===Friendlies===\n{{football box collapsib