\n| lowest attendance  = 1,561 vs [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]\n| average attendance = 4,785\n| prevseason         = [[2011\u201312 Northampton Town F.C. season|2011\u201312]]\n| nextseason         = [[2013\u201314 Northampton Town F.C. season|2013\u201314]]\n}}\nThe '''2012\u201313 season''' was [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]'s 116th season of existence and their fourth competetive season in [[Football League Two|League Two]]. Along with competing in League Two, the club also participated in the [[2012\u201313 FA Cup|FA Cup]], [[2012\u201313 Football League Cup|League Cup]] and [[2012\u201313 Football League Trophy|Football League Trophy]].\n\nThe season covers the period from 1 July 2012 to 30 June 2013.\n\n==Competitions==\n===Friendlies===\n{{football box collapsible\n|      date = {{Start date|2012|7|21|df=y}}\n|      time = 15:00 [[British Summer Time|BST]]\n|     score = 2\u20131\n|     team1 = [[Corby Town F.C.|Corby Town]]\n|    goals1 = Miller {{goal|18||42}}\n|     team2 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n|    goals2 = [[Jake Robinson|Robinson]] {{goal|69|pen.}}\n|   stadium = Steel Park\n|  location = [[Corby]]\n|attendance = 830\n|    result = L\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|      date = {{Start date|2012|7|25|df=y}}\n|      time = 19:45 [[British Summer Time|BST]]\n|     score = 0\u20134\n|     team1 = [[Cogenhoe United F.C.|Cogenhoe]]\n|    goals1 =\n|     team2 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n|    goals2 = [[Adebayo Akinfenwa|Akinfenwa]] {{goal|14}}<br>[[Michael Hoganson|Hoganson]] {{goal|34||56}}<br>[[Alex Nicholls (footballer)|Nicholls]] {{goal|77}}\n|   stadium = Compton Park\n|  location = [[Cogenhoe]]\n|attendance = tbc\n|    result = W\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|      date = {{Start date|2012|7|28|df=y}}\n|      time = 15:00 [[British Summer Time|BST]]\n|     score = 0\u20132\n|     team1 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]\n|    goals1 =\n|     team2 = [[Chelsea F.C. Unde